page.title: 01The Wildlife Around Us.
page.content: The Wildlife around us is very numerous for we don't live in a town.We have plenty of birds around us and not too many animals.The most numerous birds around here are pheasants because there is a game service which deals with up to 500,000 pheasants chicks and eggs.There are mostly foxes, stoats, weasels, rabbits, hares, rats, mice and bats.We have quite a number of finches around, because there are about 3 fir woods which support finches. There is an ornamental pond in a garden near where I live. It has teal, shelduck, tufted duck, mandarin, carolina and some others.There are a lot of mallard in Ormsby because there are three ponds. The rarest bird of prey I have seen is a sparrowhawk. There are 2 pairs of kestrels nesting in Ormsby. By Dean Mills, aged 11.
